The paper focuses on the issue of abuse in Online Social Networks (OSN), specifically Twitter. This suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Social Computing (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a custom crawler to collect a new dataset, which could fall under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of features based on users' attributes and social-graph metadata, which could fall under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
